1
00:00:00,056 --> 00:00:32,056
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:37,880 --> 00:00:40,490
[This drama is fictional and any similarity
with reality is purely coincidental.]

3
00:00:40,490 --> 00:00:42,813
[Production guidelines were followed
when filming children and animals.]

4
00:00:46,547 --> 00:00:49,213
[Episode 7]
Ah, I can finally breathe.

5
00:00:51,013 --> 00:00:53,847
But the President can't come at all?

6
00:00:53,847 --> 00:00:54,947
Well, yeah.

7
00:00:54,947 --> 00:00:56,480
Something came up.

8
00:00:56,480 --> 00:00:59,580
He's been acting like he was
going to come with you.

9
00:00:59,580 --> 00:01:01,713
I just don't like him.

10
00:01:01,713 --> 00:01:04,747
Ah, forget it. It's not like we're
that kind of close anyway.

11
00:01:04,747 --> 00:01:06,513
I was planning to come alone
in the first place.

12
00:01:06,513 --> 00:01:09,480
Ms. Jang Hui Won, please come
into the 3D ultrasound room.

13
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:10,947
Okay.

14
00:01:10,947 --> 00:01:13,147
Guardian, please come in too.

15
00:01:13,813 --> 00:01:16,347
Oh, guardian...

16
00:01:19,547 --> 00:01:21,147
I'll just walk you to the door.

17
00:01:21,147 --> 00:01:24,447
I'll watch your stuff, so don't worry.

18
00:01:24,447 --> 00:01:26,180
Okay.

19
00:01:33,713 --> 00:01:34,980
I get hot easily, that's all.

20
00:01:34,980 --> 00:01:36,147
I tend to feel warm inside.

21
00:01:36,147 --> 00:01:37,847
Give this to me.

22
00:01:37,847 --> 00:01:39,680
Thanks.

23
00:01:44,147 --> 00:01:45,147
Is it over?

24
00:01:45,147 --> 00:01:48,312
If you're still at the hospital,
I'm heading there now.

25
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:56,413
Is he still concerned?

26
00:01:58,213 --> 00:01:59,880
You don't have to come.

27
00:01:59,880 --> 00:02:01,980
It's all over.

28
00:02:13,347 --> 00:02:15,047
Why did I avoid them?

29
00:02:15,047 --> 00:02:16,613
- Do you like Jang Hui Won?
- Here.

30
00:02:16,613 --> 00:02:19,780
I plan to confess to her seriously soon.

31
00:02:24,213 --> 00:02:25,913
[Mother]

32
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:29,013
- Yes.
- Son.

33
00:02:29,013 --> 00:02:33,080
Your father just woke up. Don't worry
about us here. Focus on your work.

34
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:34,113
No.

35
00:02:34,113 --> 00:02:36,047
I'm not really needed.

36
00:02:36,047 --> 00:02:38,047
I'll go back to the hospital.

37
00:02:49,647 --> 00:02:51,213
You're going to wear it out.

38
00:02:51,213 --> 00:02:53,480
I've never seen anything like this before.

39
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:56,713
So this is the 3D ultrasound?

40
00:02:56,713 --> 00:02:58,313
I can already see

41
00:02:58,313 --> 00:03:01,580
the arms, legs, even the fingers.

42
00:03:03,447 --> 00:03:05,247
Thanks for today.

43
00:03:05,247 --> 00:03:06,913
It must have been awkward at the OB-GYN.

44
00:03:06,913 --> 00:03:09,080
Does that really matter?

45
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:12,280
What matters more is that you're not anxious.

46
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:13,280
Give me.

47
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:15,013
Okay.

48
00:03:16,147 --> 00:03:20,213
I feel like I have a lot of memories
with you tied to tteokbokki.

49
00:03:20,213 --> 00:03:22,947
When I fought with my mom
and ran away from home,

50
00:03:22,947 --> 00:03:26,180
you bought me tteokbokki.

51
00:03:26,180 --> 00:03:27,913
Right.

52
00:03:28,947 --> 00:03:30,713
I really liked that time.

53
00:03:30,713 --> 00:03:32,413
Eating tteokbokki with you,

54
00:03:32,413 --> 00:03:35,513
talking about home, grades,

55
00:03:35,513 --> 00:03:38,447
and what we wanted to do with our lives.

56
00:03:40,376 --> 00:03:41,480
Well,

57
00:03:41,480 --> 00:03:43,113
sometimes I think about this.

58
00:03:43,113 --> 00:03:46,613
If I went back to those days
with my current memories,

59
00:03:46,613 --> 00:03:49,480
wouldn't I have lived much better?

60
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:52,480
If you went back with your memories,
what would you want to do first?

61
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:53,847
Well.

62
00:03:53,847 --> 00:03:56,280
First, I'd improve my grades.

63
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:57,913
No, maybe buy a lottery ticket first?

64
00:03:57,913 --> 00:03:59,647
What?

65
00:04:00,313 --> 00:04:01,647
How about you?

66
00:04:01,647 --> 00:04:04,013
Well, I...

67
00:04:06,513 --> 00:04:08,247
I...

68
00:04:18,013 --> 00:04:22,047
I would've confessed to you first.

69
00:04:28,913 --> 00:04:31,680
I kept regretting that

70
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:33,713
maybe I waited too long.

71
00:04:35,647 --> 00:04:38,080
But after being your guardian today,

72
00:04:38,080 --> 00:04:40,213
I want to protect you even more.

73
00:04:42,447 --> 00:04:44,147
Min Uk.

74
00:04:44,847 --> 00:04:49,113
Looking back, there wasn't
a single day I didn't like you.

75
00:04:50,613 --> 00:04:52,047
I thought about it a lot.

76
00:04:52,047 --> 00:04:55,313
Who needs to be by your side right now.

77
00:04:56,147 --> 00:04:58,080
Who should be there with you.

78
00:04:58,080 --> 00:05:01,813
I wish that person were me, Hui Won.

79
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:15,280
Why does it have to be now?

80
00:05:15,280 --> 00:05:17,113
Why now?

81
00:05:28,513 --> 00:05:29,947
What brings you here at this hour?

82
00:05:29,947 --> 00:05:33,280
I came to see if you were still alive.

83
00:05:33,280 --> 00:05:35,813
Ta-da! A present.

84
00:05:35,813 --> 00:05:36,813
What is it?

85
00:05:36,813 --> 00:05:38,547
Take a look.

86
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:42,780
Wow...

87
00:05:42,780 --> 00:05:43,880
No way.

88
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:46,247
I've never received
something like this before.

89
00:05:46,247 --> 00:05:48,347
Thanks, Mi Ran.

90
00:05:48,347 --> 00:05:51,013
It's so cute.

91
00:05:51,013 --> 00:05:52,380
Cute, right?

92
00:05:52,380 --> 00:05:54,213
I feel very proud.

93
00:05:54,213 --> 00:05:56,280
I bought it last time
when I went with Min Uk.

94
00:05:56,280 --> 00:05:58,713
I forgot to give it to you
when the three of us met.

95
00:05:58,713 --> 00:06:00,947
Oh.

96
00:06:00,947 --> 00:06:02,013
With Min Uk?

97
00:06:02,013 --> 00:06:05,380
Yeah. But, I don't know what he was
so unhappy about that day.

98
00:06:05,380 --> 00:06:08,213
He barely even looked at the clothes
and left all the decisions to me.

99
00:06:08,213 --> 00:06:10,280
I shouldn't have brought him.

100
00:06:10,280 --> 00:06:13,380
Still, it paid off that I chose carefully.

101
00:06:13,380 --> 00:06:14,480
Do you like it?

102
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:16,580
Yeah.

103
00:06:16,580 --> 00:06:18,813
But he really acted like that?

104
00:06:18,813 --> 00:06:20,147
Yeah, why?

105
00:06:20,147 --> 00:06:21,947
Oh, nothing. It's nothing.

106
00:06:21,947 --> 00:06:24,813
Want something to drink?

107
00:06:28,047 --> 00:06:29,747
What's wrong with her?

108
00:06:30,613 --> 00:06:33,947
Why isn't he even replying?

109
00:06:36,180 --> 00:06:39,447
Next is the story sent by Ye Ju.

110
00:06:39,447 --> 00:06:42,913
Hello, I'm an ordinary
office worker living in Seoul.

111
00:06:42,913 --> 00:06:45,513
Ms. Jang Hui Won, please come
into the 3D ultrasound room.

112
00:06:45,513 --> 00:06:46,547
Okay.

113
00:06:46,547 --> 00:06:48,780
Guardian, please come in too.

114
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:52,713
Me, who openly opposed office romances,

115
00:06:52,713 --> 00:06:54,347
- Since when does he get to be her guardian?
- never expected it.

116
00:06:54,347 --> 00:06:56,947
And now, I'm in an office romance.
Actually, our first meeting was...

117
00:06:56,947 --> 00:06:59,413
Anyway, I'm glad the chairman is okay.

118
00:06:59,413 --> 00:07:02,647
I heard he's been eating well
since yesterday, huh?

119
00:07:02,647 --> 00:07:03,913
Who am I talking to?

120
00:07:03,913 --> 00:07:06,447
I'm lonely, so lonely.

121
00:07:06,447 --> 00:07:10,747
I thought we'd only have good days ahead,
but there's one thing that bothers me.

122
00:07:10,747 --> 00:07:15,547
My girlfriend's male best friend of 15 years.

123
00:07:15,547 --> 00:07:16,580
Oh, that can happen.

124
00:07:16,580 --> 00:07:17,847
- Turn up the volume.
- Totally.

125
00:07:17,847 --> 00:07:18,880
- Higher?
- Let's continue.

126
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:21,247
The problem is... Oh my.

127
00:07:21,247 --> 00:07:26,413
I recently found traces that my girlfriend
used to like this male friend.

128
00:07:26,413 --> 00:07:27,880
- After discovering those traces...
- Jeez.

129
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:29,747
Opening Pandora's box won't help anything.

130
00:07:29,747 --> 00:07:31,680
It'll just be picking at a scab
and making things worse.

131
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:34,747
He doesn't even know that?

132
00:07:34,747 --> 00:07:36,613
- Turn it off.
- You want it louder?

133
00:07:36,613 --> 00:07:38,113
- Are you deaf?
- And my girlfriend...

134
00:07:38,113 --> 00:07:39,680
I said turn it off, off!

135
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:41,547
- Wait a second.
- Turn it off, I said off!

136
00:07:41,547 --> 00:07:42,947
Off! Off! Turn it off!

137
00:07:42,947 --> 00:07:46,413
If you keep yelling, I get tense,
and it won't work.

138
00:07:46,413 --> 00:07:48,747
- Ugh, seriously.
- There.

139
00:07:52,947 --> 00:07:55,147
So, to sum it up,

140
00:07:55,147 --> 00:07:59,947
Option A, where a thrilling
new love arrives with ale beer,

141
00:07:59,947 --> 00:08:02,147
and Option B, a familiar yet fluttering

142
00:08:02,147 --> 00:08:04,547
male-friend and female-friend concept.

143
00:08:04,547 --> 00:08:07,113
We have to choose between the two, right?

144
00:08:07,113 --> 00:08:10,713
Content about male and female
best friends is trending these days,

145
00:08:10,713 --> 00:08:14,513
but which one best fits
our concept is the key.

146
00:08:14,513 --> 00:08:16,680
That ticklish feeling coming from familiarity

147
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:18,813
might actually be perfect for us.

148
00:08:18,813 --> 00:08:21,380
What's fluttering,
and what's perfect, exactly?

149
00:08:21,380 --> 00:08:23,047
Isn't the target audience too narrow?

150
00:08:23,047 --> 00:08:24,447
For a mass-market advertisement,

151
00:08:24,447 --> 00:08:27,580
would people without an opposite-sex
best friend even drink our beer?

152
00:08:27,580 --> 00:08:30,280
I think Option A, a new love coming your way,

153
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:33,047
seems more realistic and much better.

154
00:08:36,088 --> 00:08:38,813
Let's take a short break now.

155
00:08:41,813 --> 00:08:46,647
I also vote for Option A
about new love coming your way.

156
00:08:51,928 --> 00:08:53,880
Option A is good.

157
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:56,313
Good, Team Leader Bang.

158
00:08:56,313 --> 00:08:59,960
[Is it over? If you're still
at the hospital, I'm heading there now.]

159
00:09:11,680 --> 00:09:14,480
- Aren't you getting in?
- I... I am.

160
00:09:15,447 --> 00:09:17,547
Doors closing.

161
00:09:20,613 --> 00:09:22,480
Going up.

162
00:09:23,980 --> 00:09:26,647
I guess you were very busy that day.

163
00:09:26,647 --> 00:09:27,680
Oh, that day?

164
00:09:27,680 --> 00:09:29,013
I'm sorry I couldn't go with you.

165
00:09:29,013 --> 00:09:30,213
Something urgent came up.

166
00:09:30,213 --> 00:09:31,613
It's okay.

167
00:09:31,613 --> 00:09:36,613
Plenty of pregnant women
go to the hospital alone.

168
00:09:36,613 --> 00:09:38,780
Alone?

169
00:09:38,780 --> 00:09:41,313
That very, very urgent matter.

170
00:09:41,313 --> 00:09:43,347
Did it get resolved?

171
00:09:43,347 --> 00:09:46,580
Yes, it was something I could handle alone,

172
00:09:46,580 --> 00:09:49,380
so you don't need to worry about it.

173
00:09:55,147 --> 00:09:57,647
I have a meeting, so I'll get going.

174
00:09:59,113 --> 00:10:02,747
What? He even set a condition
just to go together.

175
00:10:02,747 --> 00:10:04,847
This is ridiculous.

176
00:10:30,680 --> 00:10:32,680
Is she hiding the fact
that they went together?

177
00:10:32,680 --> 00:10:34,480
Why bother?

178
00:10:39,213 --> 00:10:40,913
Jeez.

179
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:43,160
[Tray Return]

180
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:45,144
[Green Day]

181
00:10:45,144 --> 00:10:46,513
What's on the menu?

182
00:10:46,513 --> 00:10:48,180
Isn't dinner Korean food tonight?

183
00:10:48,180 --> 00:10:50,360
- Yeah.
- Seems right.

184
00:10:50,980 --> 00:10:52,713
- It's seaweed soup.
- Seaweed soup?

185
00:10:52,713 --> 00:10:53,880
It's good.

186
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:56,247
Why are the side dishes so skimpy?

187
00:10:56,247 --> 00:10:57,247
Tell them to put more effort in it.

188
00:10:57,247 --> 00:10:58,947
Okay.

189
00:10:59,580 --> 00:11:03,580
I'm the one who's hurt,
but why is he the one angrier?

190
00:11:09,713 --> 00:11:11,547
By the way, didn't you get ultrasound photos?

191
00:11:11,547 --> 00:11:13,847
Show me the pictures of our Yeol Mu.

192
00:11:13,847 --> 00:11:16,147
Friends really are the best.

193
00:11:17,368 --> 00:11:19,313
[President Kang Du Jun]

194
00:11:19,313 --> 00:11:20,713
[President Kang Du Jun]

195
00:11:20,713 --> 00:11:21,713
Oh my, what do I do?

196
00:11:21,713 --> 00:11:23,447
- What?
- What?

197
00:11:23,447 --> 00:11:25,047
- What?
- It's nothing.

198
00:11:25,047 --> 00:11:26,947
- It's really nothing.
- I guess she doesn't like seaweed soup.

199
00:11:26,947 --> 00:11:29,180
- Huh?
- Seems she doesn't like seaweed soup.

200
00:11:33,413 --> 00:11:34,947
[President Kang Du Jun]
What, read and ignored?

201
00:11:34,947 --> 00:11:36,213
Did he read it and ignore me?

202
00:11:36,213 --> 00:11:38,113
- Ignored it?
- Huh?

203
00:11:38,113 --> 00:11:39,313
- But it's Korean food?
- Ignore?

204
00:11:39,313 --> 00:11:42,813
Ah... nothing.

205
00:11:46,013 --> 00:11:48,247
[Jang Hui Won]
My phone's acting weird. The file won't open.

206
00:11:48,247 --> 00:11:50,780
Sometimes large files take a while to load.

207
00:11:50,780 --> 00:11:52,347
Wait a bit.

208
00:11:52,347 --> 00:11:54,080
Yeah?

209
00:11:56,013 --> 00:11:57,047
- Huh?
- Why?

210
00:11:57,047 --> 00:11:58,780
[Jang Hui Won]
It changed to deleted message.

211
00:11:58,780 --> 00:12:00,513
Maybe she sent it by accident.

212
00:12:00,513 --> 00:12:03,680
Looks like Ms. Hui Won sent it by mistake.

213
00:12:05,880 --> 00:12:08,013
Who is he texting?

214
00:12:08,013 --> 00:12:10,213
Was it sent by mistake?

215
00:12:10,213 --> 00:12:12,380
Who was she sending it to?

216
00:12:13,213 --> 00:12:14,880
I really can't stand this kind of thing.

217
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:16,913
Ah, what is it? I'm so curious.

218
00:12:16,913 --> 00:12:18,347
Should I just ask?

219
00:12:18,347 --> 00:12:20,447
Ah, whatever.

220
00:12:30,413 --> 00:12:31,880
Stop making those sounds.

221
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:34,813
Seriously, we're eating.

222
00:12:37,208 --> 00:12:38,936
Jeez.

223
00:12:47,913 --> 00:12:51,113
Should I just ask directly?

224
00:12:51,113 --> 00:12:52,248
[Jang Hui Won]

225
00:13:00,580 --> 00:13:02,713
Uncle!

226
00:13:02,713 --> 00:13:04,880
Did something happen with Manager Jang?

227
00:13:04,880 --> 00:13:05,913
Nothing happened.

228
00:13:05,913 --> 00:13:08,380
Tell me, so I can decide
whether to help you or not.

229
00:13:08,380 --> 00:13:09,813
You?

230
00:13:09,813 --> 00:13:12,213
I've probably dated
more than you have, Uncle.

231
00:13:12,213 --> 00:13:15,280
Are you secretly dating
someone behind my back?

232
00:13:15,947 --> 00:13:19,547
Stop dodging and tell me what's going on!

233
00:13:22,780 --> 00:13:25,180
Well, could it be

234
00:13:25,180 --> 00:13:28,547
Assistant Manager Cha Min Uk from Sales...

235
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,080
Forget it.

236
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:35,247
Assistant Manager Cha the honey water?

237
00:13:35,247 --> 00:13:36,247
Honey water?

238
00:13:36,247 --> 00:13:38,547
He's Manager Jang's friend.

239
00:13:38,547 --> 00:13:40,513
Don't tell me you're jealous because of him?

240
00:13:40,513 --> 00:13:42,547
You think I'd really be jealous over him?

241
00:13:42,547 --> 00:13:44,547
That's ridiculous.

242
00:13:44,547 --> 00:13:47,313
Uncle, are you jealous?

243
00:13:47,313 --> 00:13:48,813
Jealous? Don't be absurd.

244
00:13:48,813 --> 00:13:50,380
I'm Kang Du Jun.

245
00:13:50,380 --> 00:13:51,380
Would I really sink to jealousy?

246
00:13:51,380 --> 00:13:53,480
Yeah, right. No way.

247
00:13:53,480 --> 00:13:57,013
No matter what, you're
still the baby's father.

248
00:14:10,247 --> 00:14:12,347
The more I think about it,
the more absurd it is.

249
00:14:12,347 --> 00:14:14,847
How could he see that photo and not reply?

250
00:14:14,847 --> 00:14:16,513
Maybe he didn't see the photo.

251
00:14:16,513 --> 00:14:18,613
[Mi Ran]
You said you deleted it right away.

252
00:14:19,780 --> 00:14:21,313
I saw him checking his phone!

253
00:14:21,313 --> 00:14:22,813
Huh?

254
00:14:22,813 --> 00:14:26,813
Do you realize you've been talking
nonstop about your president?

255
00:14:26,813 --> 00:14:27,947
- Me?
- Yeah.

256
00:14:27,947 --> 00:14:30,547
Why are you so upset?

257
00:14:30,547 --> 00:14:32,547
You always push things like that.

258
00:14:32,547 --> 00:14:34,547
No, you're feeling upset now.

259
00:14:34,547 --> 00:14:36,680
But do you know why that is?

260
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:38,847
Because you had expectations.

261
00:14:38,847 --> 00:14:42,013
The higher your expectations,
the greater the disappointment.

262
00:14:42,013 --> 00:14:44,480
Oh, that's...

263
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:49,947
I was curious, but he acted
clueless. So I was baffled.

264
00:14:49,947 --> 00:14:51,113
Oh, please.

265
00:14:51,113 --> 00:14:54,113
Anyway, I got my bonus. I'll treat.

266
00:14:54,113 --> 00:14:55,880
Let's go eat something good with Min Uk.

267
00:14:55,880 --> 00:14:57,580
With Min Uk?

268
00:14:58,480 --> 00:15:00,680
I haven't been feeling well lately.

269
00:15:00,680 --> 00:15:03,313
I'm fine. Just treat Min Uk
to something nice.

270
00:15:03,313 --> 00:15:04,980
Yeah? Alright.

271
00:15:04,980 --> 00:15:06,713
Take good care of yourself.

272
00:15:06,713 --> 00:15:09,280
- Yeah.
- Okay.

273
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:13,380
Why do I feel like she's avoiding me?

274
00:15:24,647 --> 00:15:27,513
Whether you regret having the baby
or cry over a man,

275
00:15:27,513 --> 00:15:28,513
would you even listen if I stopped you?

276
00:15:28,513 --> 00:15:30,280
It's your life, so you handle it now.

277
00:15:30,280 --> 00:15:31,313
I'm staying out of it.

278
00:15:31,313 --> 00:15:33,047
Mom.

279
00:15:40,376 --> 00:15:42,008
[Professor Yoo]

280
00:15:50,113 --> 00:15:52,380
Yes, Professor.

281
00:15:52,380 --> 00:15:53,413
Today?

282
00:15:53,413 --> 00:15:55,680
Oh no, what should I do?

283
00:15:57,213 --> 00:16:00,047
I'm not feeling well.

284
00:16:00,047 --> 00:16:03,047
Yes, I should be fine by then.

285
00:16:04,013 --> 00:16:07,413
We can have a meal then.

286
00:16:07,413 --> 00:16:09,547
Yes, thank you.

287
00:16:21,913 --> 00:16:23,513
Any plans after work today?

288
00:16:23,513 --> 00:16:25,580
Attention everyone!

289
00:16:25,580 --> 00:16:29,280
You know we have early dismissal
today for Culture Day?

290
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:30,447
Yes!

291
00:16:30,447 --> 00:16:35,047
So I'm thinking of treating
everyone to some pork belly!

292
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:39,813
- Manager Nah?
- Oh, I'd love to join but...

293
00:16:39,813 --> 00:16:42,980
My wife said if I don't get
an early dismissal, she'll divorce me today.

294
00:16:43,613 --> 00:16:47,047
Manager Nah has three kids, so he's out!

295
00:16:50,913 --> 00:16:54,080
I have a date today.

296
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:55,280
Date?

297
00:16:55,280 --> 00:16:57,080
I booked a one-day class today.

298
00:16:57,080 --> 00:16:58,513
Oh, that knitting thing you've been learning?

299
00:16:58,513 --> 00:17:00,613
Yes, today we're knitting baby hats.

300
00:17:00,613 --> 00:17:02,513
Manager, want me to knit hats for your kids?

301
00:17:02,513 --> 00:17:03,880
Nah, my kids have big heads.

302
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:04,980
Can't make one in a day anyway.

303
00:17:04,980 --> 00:17:06,480
- Must take after their dad.
- Then, me!

304
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:07,647
- Just knit one for me.
- Assistant Manager.

305
00:17:07,647 --> 00:17:09,347
- I clearly said baby hats...
- So,

306
00:17:09,347 --> 00:17:11,680
everyone's busy, is that it?

307
00:17:11,680 --> 00:17:14,247
- Yes.
- Well then...

308
00:17:15,480 --> 00:17:17,580
- Me?
- It's not like

309
00:17:17,580 --> 00:17:20,647
I have too much time, or I'm lonely...

310
00:17:20,647 --> 00:17:22,447
No!

311
00:17:22,447 --> 00:17:25,113
Manager Jang has plans with me today.

312
00:17:32,147 --> 00:17:33,847
I already have plans.

313
00:17:36,013 --> 00:17:38,813
Honey water?

314
00:17:38,813 --> 00:17:40,680
As if he's some kind of hangover remedy.

315
00:17:48,113 --> 00:17:49,780
Mr. honey water, what brings you here?

316
00:17:49,780 --> 00:17:51,513
Pardon?

317
00:17:52,813 --> 00:17:54,680
No, Assistant Manager Cha Min Uk,
what brings you here?

318
00:17:54,680 --> 00:17:57,980
I'm not exactly free enough
to meet you one-on-one, you know.

319
00:17:57,980 --> 00:17:59,247
Who let you in?

320
00:17:59,247 --> 00:18:00,513
Without even telling me?

321
00:18:00,513 --> 00:18:02,613
It's me. Didn't you have him do something?

322
00:18:02,613 --> 00:18:04,613
He's just brought it
after finishing everything.

323
00:18:04,613 --> 00:18:05,880
- The task I assigned?
- Last time,

324
00:18:05,880 --> 00:18:08,680
you told me to redo the report, didn't you?

325
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:14,880
[Purpose of Client Visit
and Summary of Key Activities]

326
00:18:14,880 --> 00:18:17,113
I had high expectations,
but it's quite disappointing.

327
00:18:17,113 --> 00:18:20,213
If you tell me exactly what's wrong,

328
00:18:20,213 --> 00:18:21,447
I'll fix it and bring it back.

329
00:18:21,447 --> 00:18:24,247
No, I don't think it'll change
even if you redo it. No need.

330
00:18:24,247 --> 00:18:25,847
Here, something warm.

331
00:18:25,847 --> 00:18:27,580
- What is it?
- It's honey water.

332
00:18:27,580 --> 00:18:29,180
- Honey water?
- This honey water

333
00:18:29,180 --> 00:18:31,547
is mixed to a perfect golden ratio.

334
00:18:31,547 --> 00:18:33,347
Do you think I have time
for a leisurely tea break right now?

335
00:18:33,347 --> 00:18:36,580
I absolutely won't drink it. Honey water.

336
00:18:37,413 --> 00:18:39,013
I'm fine too.

337
00:18:39,013 --> 00:18:42,347
Well then, if there's nothing else,
I'll take my leave.

338
00:18:42,347 --> 00:18:45,213
I need to stop by the New Product
Development Team briefly.

339
00:18:45,213 --> 00:18:49,980
Aren't you visiting the New Product
Development Team way too often?

340
00:18:49,980 --> 00:18:52,947
Sales and New Product Development

341
00:18:52,947 --> 00:18:54,613
are inseparable, you know.

342
00:18:54,613 --> 00:18:56,313
I guess you didn't know.

343
00:18:57,013 --> 00:18:58,047
Oh, wait.

344
00:18:58,047 --> 00:19:02,047
I just remembered something
I need Assistant Manager Cha to do.

345
00:19:02,047 --> 00:19:04,547
Secretary Go, remember
what I mentioned earlier?

346
00:19:04,547 --> 00:19:06,213
Tell Assistant Manager Cha
exactly what I said.

347
00:19:06,213 --> 00:19:09,480
About what? I don't know anything about it.

348
00:19:10,647 --> 00:19:12,147
You know, that thing.

349
00:19:12,147 --> 00:19:13,147
That?

350
00:19:13,147 --> 00:19:14,913
That one, that one?

351
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:20,313
Oh, that?

352
00:19:24,180 --> 00:19:26,947
Ugh, I'm so tired of this, really.

353
00:19:26,947 --> 00:19:29,380
Ugh, neither of them is a kid.

354
00:19:32,980 --> 00:19:35,180
Emergency! Let's meet up.

355
00:19:53,413 --> 00:19:55,113
Something's off between them?

356
00:19:55,113 --> 00:19:58,547
Yes, there's definitely
some problem between them.

357
00:19:58,547 --> 00:20:00,447
It's kind of awkward.

358
00:20:00,447 --> 00:20:01,980
Come to think of it,

359
00:20:01,980 --> 00:20:04,313
Du Jun seemed in a bad mood yesterday too.

360
00:20:04,313 --> 00:20:06,147
He got annoyed over nothing.

361
00:20:06,147 --> 00:20:09,047
Am I serving a president
or raising a grumpy seven-year-old?

362
00:20:09,047 --> 00:20:12,380
Right? Manager Jang seemed
a bit more down than usual.

363
00:20:12,380 --> 00:20:13,947
Yeah.

364
00:20:13,947 --> 00:20:16,647
So what are we going to do?
Do you have a plan?

365
00:20:16,647 --> 00:20:17,780
I'll have to make one now.

366
00:20:17,780 --> 00:20:20,680
Is there anything we can do to help?

367
00:20:20,680 --> 00:20:23,180
Just in case, I made plans
with Manager after work.

368
00:20:23,180 --> 00:20:24,413
Yeah?

369
00:20:24,413 --> 00:20:26,847
Something we can help with.

370
00:20:29,180 --> 00:20:32,080
I've matched quite a few couples in my time.

371
00:20:32,984 --> 00:20:34,047
Boom.

372
00:20:34,047 --> 00:20:35,947
Love's Cupid, shall I try it again?

373
00:20:35,947 --> 00:20:38,113
Oh, Cupid?

374
00:20:38,113 --> 00:20:40,247
That sounds fun.

375
00:20:40,247 --> 00:20:43,213
Oh, how about this?

376
00:20:45,528 --> 00:20:47,313
Oh, that's perfect!

377
00:20:47,313 --> 00:20:49,413
Let's just get those two together properly.

378
00:20:49,413 --> 00:20:50,780
Then let's meet there later, okay?

379
00:20:50,780 --> 00:20:54,547
I stake my name on it.
I'll make sure to bring Kang Du Jun.

380
00:20:54,547 --> 00:20:56,447
Fighting!

381
00:20:56,447 --> 00:20:58,147
Cross!

382
00:21:01,944 --> 00:21:03,896
[Ticket Box]

383
00:21:05,213 --> 00:21:07,547
Manager, over here!

384
00:21:07,547 --> 00:21:09,480
Jeez, I told you I'll get it.

385
00:21:09,480 --> 00:21:10,947
I insisted, you know.

386
00:21:10,947 --> 00:21:13,280
It's a romance movie.
I thought you'd like it.

387
00:21:13,280 --> 00:21:15,013
Yeah.

388
00:21:16,247 --> 00:21:18,380
Oh my, just come and see.

389
00:21:18,380 --> 00:21:20,180
I said I'm busy! Why are you
bringing up a movie all of a sudden?

390
00:21:20,180 --> 00:21:23,313
I can eat alone, but I really hate
watching movies alone.

391
00:21:23,313 --> 00:21:25,180
That's ridiculous, jeez.

392
00:21:25,180 --> 00:21:26,880
Come quickly.

393
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:28,213
It'll be fun, right?

394
00:21:28,213 --> 00:21:30,447
Huh? Oh my.

395
00:21:31,832 --> 00:21:33,647
Oh.

396
00:21:33,647 --> 00:21:36,013
You two are also here.

397
00:21:36,013 --> 00:21:38,847
Oh, you two came to watch a movie too, huh?

398
00:21:38,847 --> 00:21:41,047
Our movie's at 5:30!

399
00:21:41,047 --> 00:21:42,880
Oh my gosh! Ours too!

400
00:21:42,880 --> 00:21:44,647
Oh my, what a coincidence.

401
00:21:44,647 --> 00:21:47,247
This is really amazing!

402
00:21:52,713 --> 00:21:55,413
We still have a lot of time.

403
00:21:56,152 --> 00:21:58,847
Shall we go play some
arcade games over there?

404
00:21:58,847 --> 00:22:00,513
Wow, that sounds so fun!

405
00:22:00,513 --> 00:22:03,247
Then how about we team up and bet on popcorn?

406
00:22:03,247 --> 00:22:04,247
The arcade?

407
00:22:04,247 --> 00:22:05,380
No, I'm not doing it.

408
00:22:05,380 --> 00:22:07,513
- We'll just get our clothes dirty.
- Oh, come on.

409
00:22:07,513 --> 00:22:09,180
Let's go.

410
00:22:09,180 --> 00:22:11,680
- I said no.
- Come!

411
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:13,680
Flip it, turn it over!

412
00:22:13,680 --> 00:22:16,913
Why are we doing something
so childish? Just do it.

413
00:22:20,013 --> 00:22:22,780
You're a fool if you don't!
Flip it, turn it over!

414
00:22:22,780 --> 00:22:25,176
[Du Jun, Hui Won vs Secretary Go, Se Hyeon]

415
00:22:29,368 --> 00:22:32,280
Whoa.

416
00:22:39,192 --> 00:22:40,824
Oh, no.

417
00:22:42,813 --> 00:22:44,780
How about basketball?

418
00:22:47,960 --> 00:22:49,976
Let's play a different game.

419
00:22:57,368 --> 00:22:59,064
- Come on.
- Come on.

420
00:23:02,013 --> 00:23:04,480
- Let's do something else.
- Let's do something else.

421
00:23:04,480 --> 00:23:06,780
Why? This is fun.

422
00:23:12,440 --> 00:23:14,040
Oh!

423
00:23:28,813 --> 00:23:30,513
Take it easy.

424
00:23:37,413 --> 00:23:40,180
- Don't laugh.
- Do it properly.

425
00:23:47,320 --> 00:23:48,440
[Perfect Combo]

426
00:23:51,064 --> 00:23:52,312
[Miss, Perfect]

427
00:23:52,312 --> 00:23:53,528
[Miss]

428
00:23:54,380 --> 00:23:55,447
Right!

429
00:23:55,447 --> 00:23:57,613
Right! Left!

430
00:23:59,896 --> 00:24:01,688
This is fun!

431
00:24:05,980 --> 00:24:07,947
Why is he acting like that?

432
00:24:11,680 --> 00:24:14,847
Why? I want to try this too.

433
00:24:15,947 --> 00:24:17,680
Move aside.

434
00:24:19,647 --> 00:24:21,813
Anyone can come!

435
00:24:28,313 --> 00:24:31,080
[Round 1]
Round one, fight!

436
00:24:44,413 --> 00:24:46,147
Yes!

437
00:24:53,080 --> 00:24:56,713
- Wow.
- Whoa, she's so good.

438
00:25:17,380 --> 00:25:19,080
Sorry.

439
00:25:21,047 --> 00:25:23,847
You should've brought an umbrella.

440
00:25:27,213 --> 00:25:29,780
Don't do it, don't.

441
00:25:36,780 --> 00:25:40,280
Splash all you like, it doesn't bother me!

442
00:26:44,280 --> 00:26:47,413
Movies are best enjoyed together, right?

443
00:26:47,413 --> 00:26:48,580
Aren't you all hungry?

444
00:26:48,580 --> 00:26:51,447
There's an amazing pork belly place nearby!

445
00:26:51,447 --> 00:26:53,147
Oh! Let's go! Let's go!

446
00:26:53,147 --> 00:26:55,647
Great, let's go! Go, go, go!

447
00:26:58,080 --> 00:27:00,880
If we follow them there,
we won't get home until dawn.

448
00:27:00,880 --> 00:27:02,080
Let's go this way.

449
00:27:02,080 --> 00:27:05,380
Quickly, quickly, quickly!

450
00:27:18,647 --> 00:27:21,213
If I bring up the ultrasound photo here,

451
00:27:21,213 --> 00:27:23,047
will I seem petty?

452
00:27:23,047 --> 00:27:26,947
Guess it's a bit late to ask
why she was with him that day.

453
00:27:26,947 --> 00:27:28,647
- Well...
- Well...

454
00:27:31,480 --> 00:27:33,013
You go first.

455
00:27:33,013 --> 00:27:34,980
You speak first.

456
00:27:36,947 --> 00:27:38,547
Well.

457
00:27:38,547 --> 00:27:40,113
Why aren't you asking?

458
00:27:40,113 --> 00:27:41,547
You saw everything that day, didn't you?

459
00:27:41,547 --> 00:27:43,380
Did you know that I saw it?

460
00:27:43,380 --> 00:27:45,480
I saw everything too.

461
00:27:45,480 --> 00:27:48,180
I was just pretending not to know.

462
00:27:48,180 --> 00:27:50,080
How am I supposed to ask that myself?

463
00:27:50,080 --> 00:27:51,347
Why can't you ask?

464
00:27:51,347 --> 00:27:53,213
You could've asked first, right?

465
00:27:53,213 --> 00:27:55,347
Aren't you curious?

466
00:27:55,347 --> 00:27:58,247
Is that something I'm supposed
to be curious about?

467
00:27:58,247 --> 00:28:00,913
Yeah, honestly,

468
00:28:00,913 --> 00:28:03,880
you said you liked it,
so I wanted you to see it first.

469
00:28:03,880 --> 00:28:05,313
Who? Me? Assistant Manager Cha?

470
00:28:05,313 --> 00:28:08,513
What? Why Min Uk all of a sudden?

471
00:28:10,747 --> 00:28:12,547
- What?
- What?

472
00:28:14,213 --> 00:28:17,113
What are you talking about right now?

473
00:28:17,113 --> 00:28:20,580
I was talking about the ultrasound photo.

474
00:28:22,584 --> 00:28:24,847
Jeez.

475
00:28:24,847 --> 00:28:26,047
Why are you laughing?

476
00:28:26,047 --> 00:28:28,413
So you've been talking about
the ultrasound photo this whole time?

477
00:28:28,413 --> 00:28:31,080
You didn't say a word
when you saw the message.

478
00:28:31,080 --> 00:28:34,480
When we met, you didn't even ask to see it.

479
00:28:34,480 --> 00:28:37,080
Oh, that text was the ultrasound photo?

480
00:28:37,080 --> 00:28:41,613
The file wouldn't open,
and when I checked later, it was deleted.

481
00:28:41,613 --> 00:28:44,180
Ah, then...

482
00:28:44,180 --> 00:28:45,747
Ah, caught you right now.

483
00:28:45,747 --> 00:28:48,813
I think you were seriously
misunderstanding me.

484
00:28:48,813 --> 00:28:49,847
No, it's not.

485
00:28:49,847 --> 00:28:50,847
No!

486
00:28:50,847 --> 00:28:51,913
I said no!

487
00:28:51,913 --> 00:28:55,647
Seriously, what a weird person!

488
00:28:55,647 --> 00:28:57,380
What?

489
00:29:00,047 --> 00:29:02,047
Why are you getting mad?

490
00:29:08,447 --> 00:29:12,513
How can it already be this perfect?

491
00:29:12,513 --> 00:29:13,513
Looks like it's rubbing its eyes.

492
00:29:13,513 --> 00:29:16,080
At this point, isn't it like a doll?

493
00:29:16,080 --> 00:29:18,213
You're really overreacting.

494
00:29:18,213 --> 00:29:20,347
No, it's not overreacting.

495
00:29:20,347 --> 00:29:22,747
But look at those long arms and pretty legs.

496
00:29:22,747 --> 00:29:24,380
Should we make them
take modeling lessons later?

497
00:29:24,380 --> 00:29:26,647
No, looking at the long fingers,

498
00:29:26,647 --> 00:29:29,513
piano might be good, right?

499
00:29:29,513 --> 00:29:32,080
Jeez, why are we deciding that?

500
00:29:32,080 --> 00:29:35,747
I'll let our Yeol Mu do whatever they want.

501
00:29:35,747 --> 00:29:37,447
'Our'?

502
00:29:38,713 --> 00:29:39,913
Well, the baby's dad is me, Kang Du Jun.

503
00:29:39,913 --> 00:29:40,947
Isn't it obvious?

504
00:29:40,947 --> 00:29:42,347
They will have anything they want.

505
00:29:42,347 --> 00:29:44,647
There's nothing the baby can't have.

506
00:29:48,680 --> 00:29:51,880
Oh, nice.

507
00:29:51,880 --> 00:29:54,713
The view at this hour.

508
00:29:54,713 --> 00:29:56,413
Work, home, work, home.

509
00:29:56,413 --> 00:29:58,513
It was getting predictable.

510
00:29:59,613 --> 00:30:01,147
Just say the word whenever you need.

511
00:30:01,147 --> 00:30:04,947
I'll take you anywhere.

512
00:30:09,247 --> 00:30:10,813
Well.

513
00:30:10,813 --> 00:30:15,247
About that fetal abnormality screening.

514
00:30:15,247 --> 00:30:18,980
You've looked troubled since that day.

515
00:30:18,980 --> 00:30:23,447
I wanted to ask if something happened.

516
00:30:23,447 --> 00:30:25,713
I was worried.

517
00:30:28,780 --> 00:30:31,780
Actually, my father collapsed that day.

518
00:30:31,780 --> 00:30:34,747
- What?
- He had some pre-existing conditions,

519
00:30:34,747 --> 00:30:36,747
but his blood pressure suddenly spiked.

520
00:30:36,747 --> 00:30:40,347
He got better fast, so I didn't say anything.

521
00:30:40,347 --> 00:30:41,447
I'm sorry.

522
00:30:41,447 --> 00:30:43,080
No, it's fine.

523
00:30:43,080 --> 00:30:45,780
I didn't even know.

524
00:30:45,780 --> 00:30:49,813
By the way, did you wait for me that day?

525
00:30:53,480 --> 00:30:55,613
No, I just...

526
00:30:55,613 --> 00:30:58,080
I was just curious why you couldn't come.

527
00:30:58,080 --> 00:31:00,147
You don't have to worry about it.

528
00:31:06,047 --> 00:31:07,580
By the way,

529
00:31:07,580 --> 00:31:11,113
what did you see that day, President?

530
00:31:11,113 --> 00:31:14,013
And why brought up Min Uk all of a sudden?

531
00:31:15,180 --> 00:31:16,547
That day at the hospital, were you...

532
00:31:16,547 --> 00:31:19,380
Opening Pandora's box won't help anything.

533
00:31:19,380 --> 00:31:21,280
It'll just be picking at a scab
and making things worse.

534
00:31:21,280 --> 00:31:23,647
He doesn't even know that?

535
00:31:24,747 --> 00:31:26,480
Nothing.

536
00:31:28,247 --> 00:31:29,624
[Min Uk]

537
00:31:38,580 --> 00:31:40,147
But now,

538
00:31:40,147 --> 00:31:42,880
can't you focus on me for a moment?

539
00:31:47,380 --> 00:31:50,613
A view like this isn't common at this time.

540
00:31:51,608 --> 00:31:52,856
[Decline]

541
00:32:00,180 --> 00:32:03,213
Fine, I guess everyone's too busy.

542
00:32:03,213 --> 00:32:06,747
Being nice to employees is pointless anyway.

543
00:32:10,008 --> 00:32:11,347
Ugh.

544
00:32:11,347 --> 00:32:14,313
I'm hungry, my blood sugar's dropping.

545
00:32:15,347 --> 00:32:16,613
Ah, that startled me!

546
00:32:16,613 --> 00:32:19,847
Who's there at this hour? Come in.

547
00:32:26,213 --> 00:32:27,913
I said, who is it?

548
00:32:27,913 --> 00:32:30,247
Stop joking around.

549
00:32:31,313 --> 00:32:32,947
What's this? Oh my, is it real?

550
00:32:32,947 --> 00:32:34,680
Oh my, what should I do?

551
00:32:38,780 --> 00:32:40,947
Don't mess around!

552
00:32:41,980 --> 00:32:43,747
You'll be in trouble if you keep this up!

553
00:32:48,547 --> 00:32:50,280
I'm scared.

554
00:32:55,192 --> 00:32:56,947
Ouch.

555
00:32:56,947 --> 00:32:58,547
- Oh my, oh my, Secretary Go.
- No, no.

556
00:32:58,547 --> 00:33:00,580
Oh my, goodness.

557
00:33:00,580 --> 00:33:02,547
- Why did I do that?
- It's okay.

558
00:33:02,547 --> 00:33:05,347
- No, it hurts a little, but it's fine.
- Oh, my.

559
00:33:05,347 --> 00:33:08,280
I'm really okay.

560
00:33:08,280 --> 00:33:09,547
Oh, right.

561
00:33:09,547 --> 00:33:11,447
I thought you were working late.

562
00:33:11,447 --> 00:33:14,280
[Pork Belly]
I brought some late-night snacks.

563
00:33:14,280 --> 00:33:16,113
You...

564
00:33:16,113 --> 00:33:20,947
Did you come all the way here
to give me this?

565
00:33:22,747 --> 00:33:25,780
Speaking of the pork belly,

566
00:33:25,780 --> 00:33:28,413
I personally grilled each piece

567
00:33:28,413 --> 00:33:30,013
with great care.

568
00:33:30,013 --> 00:33:32,113
Why?

569
00:33:32,113 --> 00:33:34,547
I never even asked.

570
00:33:34,547 --> 00:33:36,247
Why?

571
00:33:37,613 --> 00:33:39,413
Well...

572
00:33:47,992 --> 00:33:49,747
Oh.

573
00:33:49,747 --> 00:33:51,447
Well...

574
00:34:00,713 --> 00:34:03,180
Because you're an exceptional employee.

575
00:34:07,513 --> 00:34:09,213
Team Leader Bang.

576
00:34:24,113 --> 00:34:27,847
I came because I'm curious
about something, Jang Hui Won.

577
00:34:27,847 --> 00:34:29,447
Yes, go ahead.

578
00:34:29,447 --> 00:34:31,647
So that day at the hospital,

579
00:34:31,647 --> 00:34:33,747
- Cha...
- Cha?

580
00:34:35,513 --> 00:34:37,680
That day at the hospital, Cha...

581
00:34:37,680 --> 00:34:40,847
Cha... ah, what am I even saying?

582
00:34:40,847 --> 00:34:43,313
- Cha...
- Min Uk!

583
00:34:47,080 --> 00:34:48,813
You've been waiting long, right?

584
00:34:48,813 --> 00:34:49,947
No.

585
00:34:49,947 --> 00:34:52,913
Time flew by while I was thinking about you.

586
00:34:52,913 --> 00:34:56,313
Me too. Thinking of you,
the whole day just went by.

587
00:34:56,313 --> 00:34:58,813
Ah, come on, what are you saying?

588
00:34:58,813 --> 00:35:00,312
What are you two doing?

589
00:35:00,312 --> 00:35:04,813
Oh, I confessed to Hui Won.

590
00:35:04,813 --> 00:35:06,613
And we decided to date.

591
00:35:06,613 --> 00:35:08,247
- What?
- What are you doing before the President?

592
00:35:08,247 --> 00:35:09,747
Why, why!

593
00:35:09,747 --> 00:35:11,447
So what?

594
00:35:11,447 --> 00:35:13,513
President, you will congratulate us, right?

595
00:35:13,513 --> 00:35:14,513
You will congratulate us, won't you?

596
00:35:14,513 --> 00:35:18,513
Man to man.

597
00:35:20,480 --> 00:35:23,480
When, where, and how?

598
00:35:23,480 --> 00:35:24,547
Why, why?

599
00:35:24,547 --> 00:35:25,913
We have a date,

600
00:35:25,913 --> 00:35:27,580
so I guess we should head off now.

601
00:35:27,580 --> 00:35:29,580
Well then.

602
00:35:29,580 --> 00:35:31,080
No, Jang Hui Won.

603
00:35:31,080 --> 00:35:33,047
Jang Hui Won, wait a moment!

604
00:35:33,047 --> 00:35:34,880
- Hui Won, wait!
- What should we do today?

605
00:35:34,880 --> 00:35:36,013
Wait!

606
00:35:36,013 --> 00:35:39,247
Stop right there!

607
00:35:44,728 --> 00:35:46,328
Jeez.

608
00:35:47,013 --> 00:35:48,747
What good is just thinking about it?

609
00:35:48,747 --> 00:35:51,347
You won't even be able to ask properly.

610
00:35:52,313 --> 00:35:53,592
[Si Hyeong]

611
00:35:55,780 --> 00:35:56,880
Yeah, Si Hyeong. What's up?

612
00:35:56,880 --> 00:36:00,480
Du Jun, you know the day
the chairman collapsed?

613
00:36:10,813 --> 00:36:12,913
What brings you here? Coming at lunchtime?

614
00:36:12,913 --> 00:36:13,980
I was just in the area.

615
00:36:13,980 --> 00:36:15,513
I came by to treat you
to something delicious.

616
00:36:15,513 --> 00:36:17,447
Oh, that's kinda touching.

617
00:36:17,447 --> 00:36:18,447
Ah, by the way,

618
00:36:18,447 --> 00:36:20,147
is grandfather doing okay?

619
00:36:20,147 --> 00:36:23,347
The best medical team
is caring for him in real time.

620
00:36:23,347 --> 00:36:24,447
You don't need to worry.

621
00:36:24,447 --> 00:36:28,413
Still, I should give him a call.

622
00:36:29,347 --> 00:36:31,013
How's work?

623
00:36:31,013 --> 00:36:32,080
Nothing special, right?

624
00:36:32,080 --> 00:36:34,647
- Yeah.
- You should be done

625
00:36:34,647 --> 00:36:37,080
with your internship by now.

626
00:36:38,347 --> 00:36:39,647
So that's the real point.

627
00:36:39,647 --> 00:36:43,447
Your father started directly
in management at your age.

628
00:36:43,447 --> 00:36:46,480
You said Dad
had management training even earlier.

629
00:36:46,480 --> 00:36:48,880
So it's already late for you.

630
00:36:49,613 --> 00:36:52,447
Why did your grandfather insist
on leaving Taehan Liquor,

631
00:36:52,447 --> 00:36:55,380
which isn't even a holding company,
to your uncle?

632
00:36:55,380 --> 00:36:57,113
Eventually,

633
00:36:58,680 --> 00:37:01,213
this place is the golden egg.

634
00:37:09,980 --> 00:37:11,947
- Father.
- Yes.

635
00:37:11,947 --> 00:37:12,947
Have you eaten?

636
00:37:12,947 --> 00:37:14,447
Yeah, I have.

637
00:37:14,447 --> 00:37:16,247
I brought some samgyetang.

638
00:37:16,247 --> 00:37:18,213
It's quite good when energy is low.

639
00:37:18,213 --> 00:37:22,113
Wow, your mother would love this.

640
00:37:28,480 --> 00:37:30,680
Oh, would you like some tea too?

641
00:37:30,680 --> 00:37:33,313
I heard my sister-in-law came that day?

642
00:37:33,313 --> 00:37:35,880
Yeah, she sometimes comes to have tea.

643
00:37:35,880 --> 00:37:38,880
You're always lenient with her.

644
00:37:38,880 --> 00:37:41,447
So, what did you talk about that day?

645
00:37:49,713 --> 00:37:51,613
I'm sorry.

646
00:37:51,613 --> 00:37:52,713
I'm sorry.

647
00:37:52,713 --> 00:37:54,513
It's okay.

648
00:37:59,413 --> 00:38:03,513
Are you still taking medicine these days?

649
00:38:03,513 --> 00:38:05,147
I stopped.

650
00:38:05,147 --> 00:38:07,032
For things that could be

651
00:38:07,032 --> 00:38:09,013
used against you in the board,

652
00:38:09,013 --> 00:38:11,980
you shouldn't let anyone see or catch them.

653
00:38:11,980 --> 00:38:15,413
You know it's easy to exploit
your psychiatric history as a weakness, yes?

654
00:38:15,413 --> 00:38:18,747
Why don't you just quietly
get treatment in the U.S. like last time?

655
00:38:18,747 --> 00:38:21,147
No, I won't run away anymore.

656
00:38:21,147 --> 00:38:24,047
There won't be anything for you
to worry about anymore.

657
00:38:25,280 --> 00:38:27,513
I'll get going.

658
00:38:36,080 --> 00:38:37,380
Has he already left?

659
00:38:37,380 --> 00:38:41,580
Oh, he dropped by to give me this.

660
00:38:41,580 --> 00:38:43,580
But still,

661
00:38:43,580 --> 00:38:47,447
I was gonna bring up
the blind date while he was here.

662
00:38:59,247 --> 00:39:00,536
Oh.

663
00:39:01,368 --> 00:39:03,192
Oh.

664
00:39:08,780 --> 00:39:11,280
So, what you are saying is...

665
00:39:11,280 --> 00:39:12,747
I mean,

666
00:39:12,747 --> 00:39:15,780
let's set up your daughter with my son.

667
00:39:15,780 --> 00:39:17,780
- What?
- Our Du Jun

668
00:39:17,780 --> 00:39:19,813
may only focus on work,

669
00:39:19,813 --> 00:39:21,680
but he's not lacking in anything.

670
00:39:21,680 --> 00:39:24,113
Of course. I know that.

671
00:39:24,113 --> 00:39:27,013
But why did you choose Mi Ran

672
00:39:27,013 --> 00:39:30,013
as a match for such a precious son?

673
00:39:30,013 --> 00:39:32,913
First, her gentle way of speaking.

674
00:39:32,913 --> 00:39:35,313
You've really raised her well.

675
00:39:35,313 --> 00:39:37,980
My Mi Ran?

676
00:39:37,980 --> 00:39:43,547
You've actually talked with Mi Ran, right?

677
00:39:43,547 --> 00:39:45,980
They say one detail speaks volumes.

678
00:39:45,980 --> 00:39:50,913
Even after just a few words,
I was completely charmed.

679
00:39:53,247 --> 00:39:55,347
You're here early?

680
00:39:56,147 --> 00:39:58,047
You're really teaming up
with me for the contest?

681
00:39:58,047 --> 00:40:00,380
There are plenty of
talented people, but why me?

682
00:40:00,380 --> 00:40:04,380
Manager Nah was just bragging
to his son via video call earlier.

683
00:40:05,313 --> 00:40:08,613
It's not anyone else.

684
00:40:08,613 --> 00:40:11,613
Our team's ace offered to work together.

685
00:40:11,613 --> 00:40:13,147
Oh, Manager Nah.

686
00:40:13,147 --> 00:40:14,847
You're competent,

687
00:40:14,847 --> 00:40:16,013
and you have great drive.

688
00:40:16,013 --> 00:40:18,913
While I prefer niche challenges,

689
00:40:18,913 --> 00:40:22,447
you always consider
public appeal and marketability.

690
00:40:22,447 --> 00:40:25,013
We're going win-win together.

691
00:40:25,013 --> 00:40:26,513
Come on, fighting!

692
00:40:26,513 --> 00:40:28,347
We can do it!

693
00:40:28,347 --> 00:40:31,380
So, I've lined up someone
I think you will really like.

694
00:40:31,380 --> 00:40:35,180
A fresh perspective and vision
that our team doesn't have!

695
00:40:35,180 --> 00:40:37,313
He should be here any minute now.

696
00:40:39,064 --> 00:40:40,980
You're here!

697
00:40:56,913 --> 00:40:58,380
Assistant Manager Cha is joining too?

698
00:40:58,380 --> 00:41:00,113
We didn't invite him at first,

699
00:41:00,113 --> 00:41:02,147
but anyway, that's how it turned out.

700
00:41:02,147 --> 00:41:04,913
He never leaves Manager Jang's side.

701
00:41:04,913 --> 00:41:07,447
We're going to Gapyeong soon for research.

702
00:41:07,447 --> 00:41:09,613
It's a craft brewery Manager Jang knows well.

703
00:41:09,613 --> 00:41:11,347
Gapyeong?

704
00:41:12,880 --> 00:41:16,147
Hui Won knows good places. Smells great.

705
00:41:16,147 --> 00:41:18,980
Welcome.

706
00:41:18,980 --> 00:41:20,013
Cha Min Uk!

707
00:41:20,013 --> 00:41:21,480
Oh? Mi Ran.

708
00:41:21,480 --> 00:41:22,613
What? You came alone?

709
00:41:22,613 --> 00:41:24,580
Yeah, I was just getting takeout.

710
00:41:24,580 --> 00:41:25,912
Then let's eat together.

711
00:41:25,912 --> 00:41:29,147
I had a company dinner today,

712
00:41:29,147 --> 00:41:33,272
but Hui Won left early feeling sick.

713
00:41:33,272 --> 00:41:35,064
Oh.

714
00:41:36,080 --> 00:41:37,547
Hey, at least you answer my messages.

715
00:41:37,547 --> 00:41:38,580
It's not like I'm gonna get you or something.

716
00:41:38,580 --> 00:41:40,280
I did, just now.

717
00:41:40,280 --> 00:41:42,180
Just now?

718
00:41:42,180 --> 00:41:44,013
That's early.

719
00:41:44,947 --> 00:41:47,047
Ugh, I lost my appetite.

720
00:41:47,047 --> 00:41:48,913
I'll just get takeout too.

721
00:41:48,913 --> 00:41:50,447
- Excuse me.
- Yes.

722
00:41:50,447 --> 00:41:51,647
One more for takeout, please.

723
00:41:51,647 --> 00:41:54,280
- Okay.
- You're buying.

724
00:41:55,280 --> 00:41:57,013
What?

725
00:41:59,280 --> 00:42:00,880
Buy it for me too.

726
00:42:00,880 --> 00:42:02,613
You owe me a lot.

727
00:42:02,613 --> 00:42:05,580
You're always so slow to reply,
it's driving me nuts.

728
00:42:05,580 --> 00:42:08,213
Just because I confessed once,
you treat me like a stranger.

729
00:42:08,213 --> 00:42:10,380
That's all debt. How will you repay it?

730
00:42:10,380 --> 00:42:12,080
You're buying.

731
00:42:22,247 --> 00:42:25,547
Annoying, seriously annoying.

732
00:42:29,447 --> 00:42:32,213
- You're home.
- Ah, you scared me.

733
00:42:32,213 --> 00:42:33,313
Dad!

734
00:42:33,313 --> 00:42:36,180
I told you not to barge in when I'm not here.

735
00:42:36,180 --> 00:42:39,580
Do you really have to see your daughter
with a guy like that to finally wake up?

736
00:42:39,580 --> 00:42:40,580
Okay.

737
00:42:40,580 --> 00:42:42,113
That's not the point.

738
00:42:42,113 --> 00:42:44,347
Are you seeing anyone these days?

739
00:42:46,313 --> 00:42:47,480
Dad.

740
00:42:47,480 --> 00:42:51,547
Don't try to benefit from your daughter,
just remarry yourself.

741
00:42:51,547 --> 00:42:52,913
Just go on this one blind date,

742
00:42:52,913 --> 00:42:55,547
I promise I won't touch
any of your inheritance.

743
00:42:55,547 --> 00:42:57,580
And I'll reactivate your credit card.

744
00:42:57,580 --> 00:43:00,247
Quit working at that unprofitable hotel too.

745
00:43:00,247 --> 00:43:02,413
Really? What's this about?

746
00:43:02,413 --> 00:43:03,780
Is the family decent?

747
00:43:03,780 --> 00:43:06,480
Oh, it's beyond decent.

748
00:43:06,480 --> 00:43:10,213
First, make sure to keep it
a secret that her date is

749
00:43:10,213 --> 00:43:11,980
the second son of Taehan Group.

750
00:43:11,980 --> 00:43:13,680
Knowing him,

751
00:43:13,680 --> 00:43:16,847
he might back out if he feels pressured.

752
00:43:16,847 --> 00:43:18,547
Oh, yes.

753
00:43:19,180 --> 00:43:21,847
Just meet him once, okay?

754
00:43:25,784 --> 00:43:28,313
- No, I won't.
- Why?

755
00:43:28,313 --> 00:43:31,280
What's the point of another blind date?

756
00:43:33,213 --> 00:43:35,513
I'm seriously...

757
00:43:35,513 --> 00:43:36,680
Fine, I'll do it.

758
00:43:36,680 --> 00:43:37,813
You mean it?

759
00:43:37,813 --> 00:43:40,713
Just don't go back on your word
about the inheritance.

760
00:43:40,713 --> 00:43:42,580
Of course.

761
00:43:45,547 --> 00:43:48,080
We're going to Gapyeong soon for research.

762
00:43:48,080 --> 00:43:50,313
It's a craft brewery Manager Jang knows well.

763
00:43:50,313 --> 00:43:53,113
But how did they end up
in a team for the contest?

764
00:43:53,113 --> 00:43:56,413
And isn't Gapyeong basically a date spot?

765
00:43:59,047 --> 00:44:01,947
A date I've never even had.

766
00:44:06,580 --> 00:44:08,380
- Hello?
- Si Hyeong, are you busy?

767
00:44:08,380 --> 00:44:09,647
Yeah, really busy.

768
00:44:09,647 --> 00:44:11,380
I uploaded docs for your approval tomorrow.

769
00:44:11,380 --> 00:44:13,480
What's my schedule next Monday?

770
00:44:13,480 --> 00:44:15,713
You called this late just for that?

771
00:44:15,713 --> 00:44:18,113
It's really important to me, hurry up.

772
00:44:18,113 --> 00:44:20,247
Ugh, seriously... Wait!

773
00:44:20,247 --> 00:44:22,213
Well... this...

774
00:44:22,213 --> 00:44:23,580
Monday.

775
00:44:23,580 --> 00:44:26,713
Nothing major. Department meetings
in the morning, and...

776
00:44:26,713 --> 00:44:28,880
Then clear my schedule
if there's nothing urgent.

777
00:44:28,880 --> 00:44:30,513
Suddenly? Why? Something wrong?

778
00:44:30,513 --> 00:44:33,280
- I'm hanging up.
- Hello? Wait!

779
00:44:33,280 --> 00:44:34,980
Hello...

780
00:44:34,980 --> 00:44:37,913
Jeez.

781
00:44:42,264 --> 00:44:46,347
Oh, this feels more
like a picnic than research.

782
00:44:46,347 --> 00:44:48,680
Ah, indeed.

783
00:44:48,680 --> 00:44:51,547
Snacks and water are in the car,

784
00:44:51,547 --> 00:44:53,480
so just get in comfortably.

785
00:44:53,480 --> 00:44:58,480
Sales Team really prepares differently.

786
00:44:58,480 --> 00:45:00,213
Where's Se Hyeon?

787
00:45:00,213 --> 00:45:03,780
She said she'll print the interview materials
and come out soon.

788
00:45:04,728 --> 00:45:06,808
Oh.

789
00:45:07,647 --> 00:45:08,947
I'll go to the bathroom one last time.

790
00:45:08,947 --> 00:45:10,847
Sure.

791
00:45:14,447 --> 00:45:15,913
Hey, Hui Won.

792
00:45:15,913 --> 00:45:18,847
- Huh?
- Am I making you uncomfortable?

793
00:45:22,413 --> 00:45:24,747
I was a bit worried

794
00:45:24,747 --> 00:45:26,616
that maybe

795
00:45:26,616 --> 00:45:28,013
my confession that day

796
00:45:28,013 --> 00:45:29,304
has become a burden to you.

797
00:45:29,304 --> 00:45:33,480
No, not at all.

798
00:45:34,580 --> 00:45:36,547
You can take your time
to think about the answer.

799
00:45:36,547 --> 00:45:38,613
But during the contest,

800
00:45:38,613 --> 00:45:41,680
just treat me normally like before.

801
00:45:42,913 --> 00:45:44,613
Okay.

802
00:46:03,000 --> 00:46:04,047
Ouch.

803
00:46:04,047 --> 00:46:06,913
The straight route is great, but you're
turning too sharply at the corners.

804
00:46:06,913 --> 00:46:09,447
I told you about my back.

805
00:46:20,780 --> 00:46:24,847
- President!
- Even better seeing you all here.

806
00:46:28,547 --> 00:46:29,747
What brings you here?

807
00:46:29,747 --> 00:46:31,980
I had some business nearby,
killed two birds with one stone.

808
00:46:31,980 --> 00:46:35,380
All the way to Gapyeong?

809
00:46:35,380 --> 00:46:39,480
The owner probably expects
only approved staff to visit today.

810
00:46:39,480 --> 00:46:41,747
I think the owner would be happier

811
00:46:41,747 --> 00:46:44,447
seeing me than you, Assistant Manager Cha.

812
00:46:46,847 --> 00:46:48,980
Why are you acting like this?

813
00:46:48,980 --> 00:46:52,513
I'll explain properly to the owner.

814
00:46:52,513 --> 00:46:53,747
Oh, you're here?

815
00:46:53,747 --> 00:46:54,813
Oh, sir.

816
00:46:54,813 --> 00:46:56,480
This is the brewery owner.

817
00:46:56,480 --> 00:46:59,913
Thanks for coming all this way.

818
00:46:59,913 --> 00:47:00,980
Not at all.

819
00:47:00,980 --> 00:47:04,180
As I mentioned, please take
good care of our staff today.

820
00:47:04,180 --> 00:47:06,580
Let's talk in private when this is over.

821
00:47:06,580 --> 00:47:07,747
Yes, let's do that.

822
00:47:07,747 --> 00:47:09,180
Shall we go then?

823
00:47:09,180 --> 00:47:10,913
Yes.

824
00:47:16,313 --> 00:47:17,413
Well,

825
00:47:17,413 --> 00:47:18,580
shall we join them?

826
00:47:18,580 --> 00:47:19,780
Yeah.

827
00:47:19,780 --> 00:47:22,313
Let's go.

828
00:47:24,413 --> 00:47:27,013
On the way here,

829
00:47:27,013 --> 00:47:29,713
you saw the Texas-style
smoked barbecue place.

830
00:47:29,713 --> 00:47:32,780
And here, we have our craft beer...

831
00:47:32,780 --> 00:47:35,380
President, what brings you here?

832
00:47:35,380 --> 00:47:37,147
I came to see you.

833
00:47:37,147 --> 00:47:38,713
- What?
- Heard they have

834
00:47:38,713 --> 00:47:41,272
the best beer in town.

835
00:47:41,272 --> 00:47:42,613
Oh.

836
00:47:42,613 --> 00:47:45,547
So that's how it is.

837
00:47:48,680 --> 00:47:52,613
If you need any particular beer
or have any questions, just let me know.

838
00:47:52,613 --> 00:47:55,513
Our craft beer is real draft beer,

839
00:47:55,513 --> 00:47:57,447
with live yeast.

840
00:47:57,447 --> 00:48:00,113
I'll set it up right away.

841
00:48:00,113 --> 00:48:03,313
If you could pay more attention
to my staff than me.

842
00:48:03,313 --> 00:48:05,480
They'll call if they need anything.

843
00:48:06,313 --> 00:48:08,013
Shall we go?

844
00:48:09,913 --> 00:48:11,847
I heard the President
proposed the collaboration,

845
00:48:11,847 --> 00:48:13,947
and somehow we seem a bit sidelined.

846
00:48:13,947 --> 00:48:14,947
I know, right?

847
00:48:14,947 --> 00:48:17,780
I wish the President had come another day.

848
00:48:17,780 --> 00:48:19,647
Oh, don't be like that here.

849
00:48:19,647 --> 00:48:21,113
Let's go try some beer.

850
00:48:21,113 --> 00:48:22,247
I heard it's really good. Hurry up.

851
00:48:22,247 --> 00:48:23,880
Alright, let's go.

852
00:48:23,880 --> 00:48:26,213
Let's see how fresh it is.

853
00:48:31,080 --> 00:48:34,713
Unlike mass-produced beer from conglomerates,

854
00:48:34,713 --> 00:48:37,113
our craft beer's hallmark is its live yeast.

855
00:48:37,113 --> 00:48:40,447
This mash tun mixes malt and water,

856
00:48:40,447 --> 00:48:45,413
saccharifying them
at 60 to 80 degrees Celsius.

857
00:49:20,024 --> 00:49:21,336
[Barley]

858
00:49:23,447 --> 00:49:25,213
You gonna try non-alcoholic?

859
00:49:25,213 --> 00:49:26,947
Huh?

860
00:49:28,313 --> 00:49:30,613
Not just for pregnant women,
but for non-drinkers too.

861
00:49:30,613 --> 00:49:34,347
It'd be great if they could
enjoy beer happily.

862
00:49:34,347 --> 00:49:35,680
That's a good idea. I'm all for it.

863
00:49:35,680 --> 00:49:38,013
Let's all discuss it after research.

864
00:49:38,013 --> 00:49:40,213
- Really?
- Yeah.

865
00:49:40,213 --> 00:49:41,980
Thanks.

866
00:49:41,980 --> 00:49:44,580
How's your research going?

867
00:49:47,960 --> 00:49:51,576
Now here it is...

868
00:49:58,247 --> 00:50:00,413
Grill it properly, please.

869
00:50:04,213 --> 00:50:06,647
I confessed to Hui Won.

870
00:50:06,647 --> 00:50:09,047
Why are you telling me this now?

871
00:50:09,047 --> 00:50:10,880
Because I want to do it fairly.

872
00:50:10,880 --> 00:50:13,947
Unlike someone who created
a fake schedule just to follow her.

873
00:50:13,947 --> 00:50:17,580
Even knowing Hui Won's situation,
you still said that?

874
00:50:17,580 --> 00:50:20,047
Yes, I'm fully aware.

875
00:50:20,047 --> 00:50:22,480
And confident I can handle it.

876
00:50:22,480 --> 00:50:27,147
If you do know, you should understand
this isn't just her problem.

877
00:50:27,147 --> 00:50:31,513
To me, it just looks like
you're clinging to the past.

878
00:50:32,380 --> 00:50:33,413
I don't care.

879
00:50:33,413 --> 00:50:35,280
As long as Hui Won's okay with it.

880
00:50:35,280 --> 00:50:37,613
And let's be honest,

881
00:50:37,613 --> 00:50:39,813
I think the one caught between

882
00:50:39,813 --> 00:50:42,213
is you, not me.

883
00:50:48,347 --> 00:50:50,113
- Hui Won.
- Huh?

884
00:50:50,113 --> 00:50:52,447
- Give it to me.
- Thanks.

885
00:50:52,447 --> 00:50:55,013
Since you like bell peppers,
I prepared a lot of them.

886
00:50:55,013 --> 00:50:56,713
Really?

887
00:50:57,947 --> 00:50:59,947
- Did you wash all of this?
- Yeah.

888
00:51:08,613 --> 00:51:12,280
- These too?
- Yeah, washed them with the peppers.

889
00:51:14,780 --> 00:51:17,680
Look, ta-da!

890
00:51:17,680 --> 00:51:19,647
Wow, amazing.

891
00:51:22,713 --> 00:51:25,280
President, we prepared a small event.

892
00:51:25,280 --> 00:51:27,113
- Pretty.
- Me?

893
00:51:27,113 --> 00:51:28,813
Thank you.

894
00:51:29,947 --> 00:51:32,547
Hui Won, here.

895
00:51:34,136 --> 00:51:35,513
Oh.

896
00:51:35,513 --> 00:51:37,680
I could peel it myself.

897
00:51:37,680 --> 00:51:40,880
You never eat shrimp
because peeling them is a hassle.

898
00:51:40,880 --> 00:51:42,080
I'll do it.

899
00:51:42,080 --> 00:51:44,713
Wow, what does peeling shrimp mean?

900
00:51:44,713 --> 00:51:46,013
It's love!

901
00:51:46,013 --> 00:51:48,180
Manager Jang, you should
date a man like this!

902
00:51:48,180 --> 00:51:50,413
Oh, please!

903
00:51:50,413 --> 00:51:53,747
I peeled enough for everyone, try some.

904
00:51:53,747 --> 00:51:54,813
Please eat, here you go.

905
00:51:54,813 --> 00:51:56,513
Thank you.

906
00:51:57,447 --> 00:51:59,180
President.

907
00:52:00,713 --> 00:52:03,213
How was the beer? How was it?

908
00:52:03,213 --> 00:52:04,647
It was really good, amazing.

909
00:52:04,647 --> 00:52:06,880
Was it good?

910
00:52:06,880 --> 00:52:10,947
It's bitter yet sweet.

911
00:52:13,813 --> 00:52:16,080
Did I go too far?

912
00:52:17,747 --> 00:52:19,747
Manager, have this.

913
00:52:27,213 --> 00:52:28,913
President.

914
00:52:32,280 --> 00:52:34,980
What are you doing here?

915
00:52:34,980 --> 00:52:37,147
The night air's great,

916
00:52:37,147 --> 00:52:40,580
and the night sky is so pretty.

917
00:52:41,713 --> 00:52:45,613
You barely ate. Let's go, everyone's waiting.

918
00:52:45,613 --> 00:52:47,413
What about you, Hui Won?

919
00:52:48,347 --> 00:52:51,913
Not anyone else. Were you waiting for me?

920
00:52:51,913 --> 00:52:53,647
Pardon?

921
00:52:56,180 --> 00:52:59,180
Actually, I went to the OB-GYN that day.

922
00:52:59,180 --> 00:53:02,147
I saw you with Mr. Cha Min Uk.

923
00:53:02,880 --> 00:53:07,247
I always thought I was the one you needed.

924
00:53:07,247 --> 00:53:11,813
But today, I suddenly realized maybe I'm not.

925
00:53:11,813 --> 00:53:15,013
- President.
- I told you this before.

926
00:53:15,013 --> 00:53:16,447
I'll do as you wish.

927
00:53:16,447 --> 00:53:20,580
Whoever your heart belongs to,
it's none of my business.

928
00:53:20,580 --> 00:53:23,247
But I do expect us both
to take responsibility for our actions.

929
00:53:23,247 --> 00:53:26,613
Whoever you have feelings for, I don't care.

930
00:53:26,613 --> 00:53:29,547
I'll keep moving forward regardless.

931
00:53:29,547 --> 00:53:32,613
Whether it's one night or 15 years,
I don't care about that.

932
00:53:32,613 --> 00:53:34,380
You do what you want.

933
00:53:34,380 --> 00:53:37,713
I'll protect you two in my own way.

934
00:53:38,580 --> 00:53:42,013
I'll go ahead. Be careful on your way.

935
00:54:22,847 --> 00:54:25,713
[President Kang Du Jun]

936
00:54:28,313 --> 00:54:30,913
You do what you want.

937
00:54:30,913 --> 00:54:34,347
I'll protect you two in my own way.

938
00:54:43,680 --> 00:54:45,747
What I said earlier...

939
00:54:47,547 --> 00:54:49,980
How's your research going?

940
00:54:50,648 --> 00:54:52,313
Since you like bell peppers...

941
00:54:52,313 --> 00:54:54,447
I think the one caught between

942
00:54:54,447 --> 00:54:56,747
is you, not me.

943
00:54:58,808 --> 00:54:59,928
[Jang Hui Won]

944
00:55:11,113 --> 00:55:13,780
The draft beer there was insane!

945
00:55:13,780 --> 00:55:15,313
It's not that the beer yeast is alive,

946
00:55:15,313 --> 00:55:17,480
[Seriously]
it was seriously alive.

947
00:55:17,480 --> 00:55:19,113
I was drinking like crazy
and almost got wasted!

948
00:55:19,113 --> 00:55:20,913
He really was drinking nonstop.

949
00:55:20,913 --> 00:55:22,080
Right? I drank a lot, didn't I?

950
00:55:22,080 --> 00:55:24,913
You didn't go for research but for fun, huh?

951
00:55:24,913 --> 00:55:26,713
- Assistant Manager Choi.
- I heard from Se Hyeon

952
00:55:26,713 --> 00:55:28,013
that the President came too, huh?

953
00:55:28,013 --> 00:55:30,180
Yeah, he got out of a car wearing a suit,

954
00:55:30,180 --> 00:55:31,313
and I thought he was a model.

955
00:55:31,313 --> 00:55:33,147
People who've modeled are different.

956
00:55:33,147 --> 00:55:34,813
But it was supposed to be just staff,

957
00:55:34,813 --> 00:55:38,147
so it must've been a bit awkward
seeing the President, huh?

958
00:55:38,147 --> 00:55:39,347
I thought it would be awkward for me too.

959
00:55:39,347 --> 00:55:41,913
But thanks to him, we did
the research comfortably,

960
00:55:41,913 --> 00:55:44,213
had a campfire,

961
00:55:44,213 --> 00:55:45,647
and totally spoiled ourselves.

962
00:55:45,647 --> 00:55:46,647
He seemed really uncomfortable though.

963
00:55:46,647 --> 00:55:49,080
Plus the President really liked me!

964
00:55:49,080 --> 00:55:50,980
I have extraordinary sense, right?

965
00:55:50,980 --> 00:55:53,447
Your perception is uniquely special.

966
00:55:53,447 --> 00:55:55,947
Right? Isn't that true, Se Hyeon?

967
00:55:55,947 --> 00:55:58,180
Absolutely. Completely unique.

968
00:55:58,180 --> 00:55:59,580
Exactly.

969
00:55:59,580 --> 00:56:00,680
Se Hyeon's completely deadpan about this.

970
00:56:00,680 --> 00:56:04,680
True, we should ask Manager Jang
who was actually there.

971
00:56:07,180 --> 00:56:08,980
Huh? Where'd Manager Jang go?

972
00:56:08,980 --> 00:56:10,180
She was here seconds ago.

973
00:56:10,180 --> 00:56:12,113
Oh, she left with a file earlier.
Guess she has something to report.

974
00:56:12,113 --> 00:56:14,213
As expected, after visiting
the brewery yesterday,

975
00:56:14,213 --> 00:56:16,180
Manager Jang is full of inspiration again.

976
00:56:16,180 --> 00:56:17,180
Well, that won't do.

977
00:56:17,180 --> 00:56:18,180
I can't just stay still.

978
00:56:18,180 --> 00:56:20,413
I got inspired too.

979
00:56:21,213 --> 00:56:23,047
Inspiration?

980
00:56:23,047 --> 00:56:24,047
[Assistant Manager Cha Min Uk]

981
00:56:24,047 --> 00:56:26,380
As I mentioned, there's only one condition.

982
00:56:26,380 --> 00:56:29,480
When ordering soju or beer,
mention our product first.

983
00:56:29,480 --> 00:56:33,147
If you follow that, we'll supply
all liquor at agreed prices.

984
00:56:33,147 --> 00:56:34,680
Agreed.

985
00:56:34,680 --> 00:56:36,780
- Thank you.
- I'll go now.

986
00:56:36,780 --> 00:56:38,413
Heard Taehan Group's heir is coming today.

987
00:56:38,413 --> 00:56:41,380
He's the President from
the beer commercial, right? Kang Du Jun?

988
00:56:41,380 --> 00:56:42,513
Looks like he's having a blind date.

989
00:56:42,513 --> 00:56:44,980
Really? I wonder who he's meeting.

990
00:56:44,980 --> 00:56:46,080
Probably a celebrity?

991
00:56:46,080 --> 00:56:47,147
Could be.

992
00:56:47,147 --> 00:56:50,147
With that kind of wealth and looks...

993
00:56:51,847 --> 00:56:52,847
Are you sure?

994
00:56:52,847 --> 00:56:55,513
Are you really sure he's going
on a blind date?

995
00:57:03,513 --> 00:57:05,464
[Hui Won]

996
00:57:14,680 --> 00:57:17,180
Oh, here to see the President?

997
00:57:17,180 --> 00:57:19,247
Ah, yes... is he...

998
00:57:19,247 --> 00:57:21,813
He has a meeting outside the company today
and will leave directly from there.

999
00:57:21,813 --> 00:57:23,080
Have you tried contacting him?

1000
00:57:23,080 --> 00:57:24,113
I can give him a call.

1001
00:57:24,113 --> 00:57:26,247
No, it's fine.

1002
00:57:36,013 --> 00:57:37,464
[Min Uk]

1003
00:57:45,713 --> 00:57:48,413
President Kang Du Jun is
going on a blind date today.

1004
00:57:48,413 --> 00:57:51,347
After all this, it's still Kang Du Jun?

1005
00:57:52,947 --> 00:57:55,813
I know what you're struggling with.

1006
00:57:55,813 --> 00:57:58,080
All I can say right now is this.

1007
00:57:58,080 --> 00:58:00,347
I won't let you

1008
00:58:00,347 --> 00:58:03,480
face any situation alone.

1009
00:58:03,480 --> 00:58:07,647
And I will absolutely never

1010
00:58:07,647 --> 00:58:09,447
let go of your hand again.

1011
00:58:09,447 --> 00:58:13,180
I wasn't sure how to define this
until I said it out loud, but now I'm sure.

1012
00:58:13,180 --> 00:58:15,747
To be precise, it's because I like you.

1013
00:58:15,747 --> 00:58:19,213
Whoever you have feelings for, I don't care.

1014
00:58:19,213 --> 00:58:21,680
I'll keep moving forward regardless.

1015
00:58:21,680 --> 00:58:24,713
He said he likes me,
and he'd keep going straight.

1016
00:58:24,713 --> 00:58:27,813
But now a blind date?

1017
00:58:36,513 --> 00:58:38,747
Taxi! Taxi!

1018
00:58:52,013 --> 00:58:53,947
I need to get home by 8.

1019
00:58:53,947 --> 00:58:55,747
I won't take up much of your time.

1020
00:58:55,747 --> 00:58:58,213
Anyway, if it's work,
you handle it all alone.

1021
00:58:58,213 --> 00:59:00,680
Son, do I even have to beg you

1022
00:59:00,680 --> 00:59:02,747
to have dinner with me?

1023
00:59:02,747 --> 00:59:04,747
Fine.

1024
00:59:04,747 --> 00:59:07,880
But you said casual meal. Why here?

1025
00:59:07,880 --> 00:59:09,613
Hello.

1026
00:59:09,613 --> 00:59:12,113
- Hello.
- You're here.

1027
00:59:21,400 --> 00:59:24,024
[Yeonbingwan Restaurant]

1028
00:59:31,413 --> 00:59:34,080
No, you're feeling upset now.

1029
00:59:34,080 --> 00:59:36,147
But do you know why that is?

1030
00:59:36,147 --> 00:59:37,513
Because you had expectations.

1031
00:59:37,513 --> 00:59:41,613
The higher your expectations,
the greater the disappointment.

1032
01:00:17,447 --> 01:00:20,613
What? Why are you here, Jang Hui Won?

1033
01:00:20,613 --> 01:00:23,380
Well, I...

1034
01:00:35,180 --> 01:00:37,380
Don't do this blind date.

1035
01:00:43,680 --> 01:00:45,580
I like you.

1036
01:02:19,680 --> 01:02:21,613
You look pretty today.
Makes me want to ask you out.

1037
01:02:21,613 --> 01:02:23,747
Why don't you try kidnapping me then?

1038
01:02:23,747 --> 01:02:24,747
- Is that your boyfriend?
- Pardon?

1039
01:02:24,747 --> 01:02:25,813
Manager Jang, do you have a boyfriend?

1040
01:02:25,813 --> 01:02:26,947
I like the President.

1041
01:02:26,947 --> 01:02:28,047
I knew it.

1042
01:02:28,047 --> 01:02:29,480
And I don't think this is over yet.

1043
01:02:29,480 --> 01:02:31,147
If she's a woman you brought,

1044
01:02:31,147 --> 01:02:33,680
even my late husband would have liked her.

1045
01:02:33,680 --> 01:02:36,280
What's your purpose
in approaching Jang Hui Won?

1046
01:02:36,280 --> 01:02:38,080
Big news, big news!

1047
01:02:38,080 --> 01:02:39,580
Haven't you all seen the Office Talk chat?

1048
01:02:39,580 --> 01:02:41,113
If it were me, I couldn't come to work.

1049
01:02:41,113 --> 01:02:42,513
You were the one who crossed the line.

1050
01:02:42,513 --> 01:02:44,547
Now I'll protect my loved ones too.

1051
01:02:44,547 --> 01:02:45,592
[Anonymous board]
I'll be looking forward to it.

1052
01:02:45,592 --> 01:02:48,580
You'll have to do your best to protect them.
